snippet.textDisplay: what's weird is most consumer thinks that more MEGAPIXEL is better, well yes but no. It's all about the sensor size, a 108 MP with a sensor smaller than a pinky nail will not compare to a 24 megapixel entry level camera with APS-C sensor. I've heard some people talk about their phone having all these crazy megapixel and then laugh at a real camera not having even half the megapixel. A 108MP camera on a phone is nice to have sure but if you have a last gen phone and want to upgrade to a new phone that is over a $1000 mainly because of its camera, do yourself a favor and just buy a real camera,  a small mirrorless can fit in your pocket or purse and won't be too bulky, something like the Fujifilm X100f would be a great start.
